cs.PL, cs.CT, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses functional programming languages and provides a Haskell implementation. 
- cs.CT (Category Theory): The paper heavily relies on category theory, specifically Tambara modules and V-enriched categories. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper deals with data transformation patterns and accessors, which can be seen as a form of logical reasoning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses accessing subfields and iterating over containers, which are common operations in data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper provides a practical implementation of the theoretical concepts discussed.
